0.1.0
- Initial CombatManager mod shell.
- Added passive AI intent visualizer toggled with Ctrl+Shift+C in build mode.

0.1.1
- Converted the overlay into a standalone AI sandbox.
- Added target-centered circle, point-at, and broadside presets.
- Added one-shot Import Current AI seeding and a resizable grid-first UI.

0.1.2
- Reworked the overlay into an opaque tactical console.
- Expanded the grid to fill rectangular viewports while keeping target-centered scale.
- Added clearer orbit/craft/target drawing, zoom, fit orbit, trail, legend, and collapsed import details.

0.1.3
- Added simulated target profiles and target path modes.
- Added craft pursuit state with speed, acceleration, and turn-rate controls.
- Mirrored AI steer-point planners for circle, point-at, broadside, and Naval 2.0 sandbox behaviour.

0.1.4
- Added a shared behaviour planner layer with raw steer point, finite motion point, desired facing, range, side/state, and approximation notes.
- Split sandbox pursuit into ship/tank, hover/six-axis, and airplane movement-card models.
- Added scenario presets, raw steer/motion-point grid toggles, and selected-mainframe one-shot import.

0.1.5
- Reworked the sandbox into a symmetric Blue-vs-Red AI duel simulator.
- Added mainframe-like behaviour and manoeuvre settings for both simulated entities.
- Added shared ship/tank, hover, six-axis, and airplane manoeuvre simulation used by both sides.
- Kept import one-shot and Blue-only; Red remains manually configured inside the sandbox.

0.1.6
- Reworked the duel sandbox into a fullscreen editor layout.
- Moved Blue/player controls to a fixed left panel and Red/enemy controls to a fixed right panel.
- Moved scenario, playback, zoom, fit, and overlay toggles into a compact top toolbar.
- Added independent side-panel scrolling and layout verification for 1280x720 and wide screens.

0.1.7
- Polished the fullscreen HUD for readability.
- Replaced always-expanded side panels with tabbed Blue and Red controls.
- Increased panel width, text size, button height, and slider label/value spacing.
- Simplified the toolbar into grouped scenario, playback, and view controls.
- Added opaque graph label backplates and reduced default graph text clutter.
